                | Now we have to go to our dashboard&comma; head over to
                a(href='https://dashboard.heroku.com/apps') https&colon;&sol;&sol;dashboard&period;heroku&period;com&sol;apps
                | and login&period;  You should see the app the you just created&comma; though it probably doesn&apos;t work yet&period;  Then click on your current application&comma; and in the next page&comma; click &quot;New Add-ons&period;&quot;
            p.lead
              | In this long list of add-ons&comma; feel free to add whatever you like&comma; but for the website&apos;s sake&comma; scroll to MongoLab&comma; and add it for your app specifically&period;  Note that we&apos;ve actaully already added the capability to integrate with MongoLab from the way that we established a connection to it here-
            pre.prettyprint.
               var uristring = process.env.MONGOLAB_URI;              
            p.lead
              | We&apos;re finally ready to make our application live with MongoDB capabilities&comma; Go to yourapp&period;herokuapp&period;com
          .row.featurette
            .col-md-9.col-md-offset-1
